		<div class="courseListDescription">This course builds on the knowledge gained in MHR 523. It is designed to develop the student's knowledge, skills, and abilities in three significant integrated Human Resource areas: job analysis, recruitment, and selection. Students will conduct a job analysis, investigate recruitment strategies and develop a job advertisement; examine various selection tools; and practice interviewing simulated job applicants. The course uses an experiential learning design, and students have opportunities to practice skills that are central to effective hiring decisions.</div>
	
	
